comments.body:
@italobusi @boucadair For points 6)，I do not think “ietf-tp-interface-reference-topology” model is the right approach. [](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/draft-ietf-ccamp-if-ref-topo-yang-01#section-3.2) because interface-ref is device local. Therefore, here in the inventory topology model, we follow the definition as Layer 2 Network Topologies rfc8944  and Layer 3 Network Topologies rfc 8346. And it's necessary to map between the termination point, the physical port, and the specific interface, right?

point 7)
Current YANG model design has a one-to-one relationship between the abstract node and the physical NE, as well as between the termination point and the link. I think the model looks quite straightforward. We can clarify this if you think it's necessary
